{"title":"SaddleDonut Pro puts a bubbly cushion on your bike seat","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/09/13/cushion-aid-saddledonut-pro/","date":1631570633000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><img width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13165617/Cushion-Aid-SaddleDonut-bicycle-seat-padding-3-800x600.jpg?ezimgfmt=rs%3Adevice%2Frscb28-1\" alt=\"cushion aid saddle donut bike seat cushion stuck on a racing saddle\" loading=\"eager\" srcset=\"\" sizes=\"\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\"><header></header><p>Support us! BikeRumor may earn a small commission from affiliate links in this article. <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/privacy\" target=\"_blank\">Learn more</a>.</p></div><div role=\"main\"><article id=\"post-271391\" role=\"article\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/BlogPosting\"><section itemprop=\"text\"><p>Whether riding on trail, gravel or smooth roads, long days in the saddle can be murder on your backside. Or, rather, your <em>under</em>-side. Even the best-designed saddles can rub riders the wrong way, leading to chafing, saddle sores, and all manner of aches and pains.</p><p>The post-ride waddles may be a laughing matter for cyclists who have been down these dark roads, but for Cushion-Aid, it’s not. So they did something about it…</p><p><iframe loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1200\" height=\"675\" data-ezsrc=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/fspeZghe5Co?version=3&amp;rel=1&amp;showsearch=0&amp;showinfo=1&amp;iv_load_policy=1&amp;fs=1&amp;hl=en-US&amp;autohide=2&amp;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation\"></iframe></p><p>Basically, the SaddleDonut is a simple device that sticks onto <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2019/07/12/everything-you-need-to-know-about-saddles-part-5-finding-the-best-shape-for-you/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">any saddle</a>, with versions for men’s, women’s, and triathlon-style saddles. It is designed to place plush bubbles over the parts of a saddle that have the most intense contact with riders, directly under the sit bones. Not only does it add cushion, but it reduceslipping, chafing and the irritation and pain that movement can cause.</p><p>In fact, they say the stability it provides also keeps you hammering the pedals rather than awkwardly shifting around or standing every few miles, daydreaming about Gold Bond.</p><div id=\"attachment_271396\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13170026/Cushion-Aid-SaddleDonut-bicycle-seat-padding-4.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-271396\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13170026/Cushion-Aid-SaddleDonut-bicycle-seat-padding-4.jpg\" alt=\"Cushion-Aid SaddleDonut bike seat cushions for men women and triathletes\" width=\"2000\" height=\"535\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13170026/Cushion-Aid-SaddleDonut-bicycle-seat-padding-4.jpg 2000w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13170026/Cushion-Aid-SaddleDonut-bicycle-seat-padding-4-297x79.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13170026/Cushion-Aid-SaddleDonut-bicycle-seat-padding-4-800x214.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13170026/Cushion-Aid-SaddleDonut-bicycle-seat-padding-4-120x32.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13170026/Cushion-Aid-SaddleDonut-bicycle-seat-padding-4-768x205.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13170026/Cushion-Aid-SaddleDonut-bicycle-seat-padding-4-1536x411.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13170026/Cushion-Aid-SaddleDonut-bicycle-seat-padding-4.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13170026/Cushion-Aid-SaddleDonut-bicycle-seat-padding-4.jpg 2000w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13170026/Cushion-Aid-SaddleDonut-bicycle-seat-padding-4-297x79.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13170026/Cushion-Aid-SaddleDonut-bicycle-seat-padding-4-800x214.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13170026/Cushion-Aid-SaddleDonut-bicycle-seat-padding-4-120x32.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13170026/Cushion-Aid-SaddleDonut-bicycle-seat-padding-4-768x205.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/13170026/Cushion-Aid-SaddleDonut-bicycle-seat-padding-4-1536x411.jpg 1536w\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-271396\">Left to right: Men’s, Women’s, and Triathlon saddle versions.</p></div><p>Christian Echavarria, the creator of the Cushion-Aid SaddleDonut, said he was inspired to create the cushion after experiencing awful saddle sores during the 3,000-mile <a href=\"https://www.raceacrossamerica.org/phone/index.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Race Across America (R.A.A.M.)</a>. MSRP is $40, available now with free shipping worldwide.</p><p><a href=\"http://www.cushion-aid.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>Cushion-Aid.com</em></a></p></section></article></div></div>","author":"Mark Wilson","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0